Titolo: Perestroika (video game)

Anno: 1990

Descrizione: Perestroika (also known as Toppler) is a Soviet video game released in 1990 by a small software developer called Locis (Nikita Skripkin, Aleksander Okrug and Dmitry Chikin, currently - Nikita online) in 1990, and named after Mikhail Gorbachev's policy of Perestroika. The music playing on the title screen is a Russian folk song Dubinushka from the 19th century.

Genere: Non specificato


Valutazione: N/A
